topic.title: Port Equalization Status Command

body.p: MRPC Command ID: 0x16

p.b: Sub Command: Local Tx Coefficient Dump

body.p: This Sub Command is used to dump local transmitter coefficient after a successful equalization process.

table.title: Sub Command_Local Tx Coefficient Dump Input Data

body.p: 0x00： Local Tx Coefficient Dump
0: Per port operation; 1: Per lane operation
If per port operation is selected, all the parameters will be applied to all the lanes in current port.
Physical port id, 0-51
Logical lane ID in current physical port, 0 - maximum link width
Only valid when operation type is 1

table.title: Sub Command_Local Tx Coefficient Dump Output Data

note.p: Coefficient value of Lane 1-Lane N are only valid when Op Type = 0 (Per-port)

body.p: 0x00： Local Tx Coefficient Dump
0: Per port operation; 1: Per lane operation
If per port operation is selected, all the parameters will be applied to all the lanes in current port.
Physical port id, 0-51
Maximum lane id when Op Type is 0
Logical lane ID in current physical port when Op Type is 1

p.b: Sub Command: Dump Far-end Transmitter Settings

body.p: This Sub Command is used to dump far-end transmitter coefficient after a successful equalization process.

p.b: Sub Command: Far-end TX Equalization Table Dump

body.p: This Sub Command is used to dump the equalization process for the far-end transmitter which is captured in EQ_TABLE.

table.title: Sub Command_Far-end TX Equalization Table Dump Input Data

body.p: 0x02： Far-end TX Equalization Table Dump
Physical port id, 0-51

table.title: Sub Command_Far-end TX Equalization Table Dump Output Data

body.p: 0x02: Far-end TX Equalization Table Dump
Physical port id, 0-51
Current lane id to dump EQ_Table from
Steps of last equalization process
Pre-Cursor applied to far-end transmitter in a step of lane equalization.
Post-Cursor applied to far-end transmitter in a step of lane equalization.

1:Error; 0:No Error
1:Lane was part of the link; 0:Lane was not part of the link

This Sub Command is used to dump the tuning method that is currently used.

table.title: Sub Command_Dump Equalization Tuning Method Input Data
Sub Command_Dump Equalization Tuning Method Output Data

li.p: When tune method is "Preset", it represents "maximum preset"
When tune method is "Algorithm", it represents "maximum Pre-Cursor"
When tune method is "Table", it represents "maximum Table Index"
Only valid when tune method is "Algorithm", working together with "Maximum Pre-Cursor"
Only valid when tune method is "Preset', COEF will be internally converted from the preset value before send with EQ TS1/TS2
Only valid when tune method is "Algorithm", it represent the step size. The pre-cursor/post-cursor will be increased by the step size each time.

p.b: Only valid when tune method is "Table". One table entry is composed of the three items.
